  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8 03\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Electricity bill comes in 03 ways",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is stated in a statement that instead of the method of giving pre-printed bills that has been followed so far in issuing electricity bills, the Ceylon Electricity Board has taken steps to introduce three new methods.",
        "Accordingly, the following methods will be used in issuing monthly electricity bills to customers in the future.",
        "1. Issuance of printed bills using thermal paper (thermal printed bills) \u2014 If there are customers who expect some kind of physical bill, this bill will be issued to them during monthly bill reading.",
        "2. By SMS (SMS) \u2014 After reading the monthly bill, the monthly electricity bill will be sent to the phone number registered with CEB through SMS. To register for this, you can get the assistance of the CEB representative who comes to the premises to read the manu. Or you can register yourself by texting 1987 using \u201cREG<space>ten digit electricity account number\u201d.",
        "3. CEBCare Mobile App \u2013 The facility of receiving the bill after reading the monthly bill is also provided using the CEBCare mobile app.",
        "These three new methods of issuing bills were introduced as one more step in the \"CEB Assist\" program, which aims to provide a more efficient customer service as well as computerize corporate affairs, and issuing e-bills by e-mail as the fourth method of sending bills. They say that the necessary technical arrangements are currently being made.",
        "The decision to implement this program was based on the fact that pre-printing and distribution of electricity bills is not possible due to the current shortage of paper, and resorting to these new methods will not only increase efficiency, but also save more than a billion rupees per year in a background where the cost of printed bills has increased. Ceylon Electricity Board further mentions that it will also contribute to"
      ],
